summary: This module provides functions to encapsulate multiple body parts such as attachments into a single message. The communication of such messages follow the MIME (Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions) specification as specified in the RFC 2045 standard.
description:
Module Overview

This module provides functions to encapsulate multiple body parts such as attachments into a single message. The communication of such messages follow the MIME (Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions) specification as specified in the RFC 2045 standard.

Entity refers to the header fields and the content of a message or a part of the body in a multipart entity.

Modify and retrieve the data in an entity

This module provides functions to set and get an entity body from different kinds of message types such as XML, text, JSON, byte[], and body parts. Headers can be modified through functions such as addHeader(), setHeader(), removeHeader(), etc.

For information on the operations, which you can perform with this module, see the below Functions. For examples on the usage of the operations, see the Request with multiparts Example and Response with multiparts Example.

parameters.name: entityBody
parameters.description: Entity body can be of the type string,xml,json,byte[],io:ReadableByteChannel, or Entity[].

methods.name: setBody
methods.description:
Sets the body of the entity with the given content. Note that any string value is set as text/plain. To send a JSON-compatible string, set the content-type header to application/json or use the setJsonPayload method instead.

 mimeEntity.setBody("body string");

parameters.name: filePath
parameters.description: Path of the file

parameters.name: contentType
parameters.description: Content type to be used with the payload. This is an optional parameter. The default value is application/octet-stream

methods.name: setFileAsEntityBody
methods.description:
Sets the entity body with a given file. This method overrides any existing content-type headers with the default content-type, which is application/octet-stream. This default value can be overridden by passing the content type as an optional parameter.

 mimeEntity.setFileAsEntityBody("<file path>");

parameters.name: jsonContent
parameters.description: JSON content, which needs to be set to the entity

parameters.name: contentType
parameters.description: Content type to be used with the payload. This is an optional parameter. The default value is application/json

methods.name: setJson
methods.description:
Sets the entity body with the given json content. This method overrides any existing content-type headers with the default content-type, which is application/json. This default value can be overridden by passing the content type as an optional parameter.

 mimeEntity.setJson({ "Hello": "World" });

returnParameters.description: json data extracted from the entity body or else an mime:ParserError if the entity body is not a JSON

methods.name: getJson
methods.description: Extracts the JSON body from the entity.

parameters.name: xmlContent

parameters.name: contentType

methods.name: setXml
methods.description:
Sets the entity body with the given XML content. This method overrides any existing content-type headers with the default content-type, which is application/xml. This default value can be overridden by passing the content-type as an optional parameter.

 mimeEntity.setXml(xml `<hello> world </hello>`);

returnParameters.description: xml data extracted from the entity body or else an mime:ParserError if the entity body is not an XML

methods.name: getXml
methods.description: Extracts the xml body from the entity.

methods.name: setText
methods.description:
Sets the entity body with the given text content. This method overrides any existing content-type headers with the default content-type, which is text/plain. This default value can be overridden by passing the content type as an optional parameter.

methods.description: Extracts the text body from the entity. If the entity body is not text compatible, an error is returned.

constants.name: LEADING
constants.description: Header is placed before the payload of the request/response.

constants.name: TRAILING
constants.description: Header is placed after the payload of the request/response.

constants.name: BOUNDARY
constants.description: Key name for boundary parameter in MediaType. This is needed for composite type media types.

constants.name: START
constants.description: Key name for start parameter in MediaType. This determines which part in the multipart message contains the payload.

constants.name: TYPE
constants.description: Key name for type parameter in MediaType. This indicates the MIME media type of the root body part.

constants.name: CHARSET
constants.description: Key name for charset parameter in MediaType. This indicates the character set of the body text.

constants.name: DEFAULT_CHARSET
constants.description: Default charset to be used with MIME encoding and decoding.

unionTypes.name: HeaderPosition
unionTypes.description:
Defines the position of the headers in the request/response.

LEADING: Header is placed before the payload of the request/response TRAILING: Header is placed after the payload of the request/response
